          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12659205/comment/13883294",
            "id": "13883294",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jlowe",
              "name": "jlowe",
              "key": "jlowe",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Jason Darrell Lowe",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Chicago"
            },
            "body": "Ran into another case where a user filled a disk with a large stdout/stderr, and the NM took forever to recover the disk since it was trying to aggregate the huge file to HDFS.  Not only was this a waste of HDFS space and network bandwidth, but ops were unable to manually recover easily by removing the large logfile.  The NM process was holding the file open during log aggregation, so the disk space was not able to be freed until either the NM finished aggregating or the NM process exited.\n\nMany users would prefer the ability to grab a configurable number of bytes at the head of a large log and a number of bytes at the end of the large log.  Of course the NM would need to inject some text into the log to indicate it was truncated, and bonus points if it includes the original log size and/or the amount that was truncated.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jlowe",
              "name": "jlowe",
              "key": "jlowe",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Jason Darrell Lowe",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Chicago"
            },
            "created": "2014-01-27T21:01:56.183+0000",
            "updated": "2014-01-27T21:01:56.183+0000"
          },
