        "id": "17194507",
        "author": {
          "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=epayne",
          "name": "epayne",
          "key": "eepayne",
          "avatarUrls": {
            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=eepayne&avatarId=40831",
            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=eepayne&avatarId=40831",
            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=eepayne&avatarId=40831",
            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=eepayne&avatarId=40831"
          },
          "displayName": "Eric Payne",
          "active": true,
          "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
        },
        "body": "[~adam.antal], are you still planning on working on this JIRA?\r\n\r\nbq. Ran into another case where a user filled a disk with a large stdout/stderr, and the NM took forever to recover the disk\r\nbq. +1 on the idea of limiting the size of log aggregation. We should have someway to truncate (front & tail) the log contents if it is really large.\r\n\r\nIt seems that there are a couple of requirements for this feature.\r\n# Prevent logs for any container from becoming larger than a configurable size.\r\n# Truncate everything from the middle of large log files, leaving a configurable amount of the head and the tail.\r\n\r\nInternally, we have implemented the former by allowing system admins to specify a configurable max log size per container.\r\n",
        "updateAuthor": {
          "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=epayne",
          "name": "epayne",
          "key": "eepayne",
          "avatarUrls": {
            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=eepayne&avatarId=40831",
            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=eepayne&avatarId=40831",
            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=eepayne&avatarId=40831",
            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=eepayne&avatarId=40831"
          },
          "displayName": "Eric Payne",
